title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message:
No liquid damage, J8500 in perfect condition.
MacBook came with cracked display (there was still image/backlight)
New screen fitted, Apple logo, progress bar and then blank screen.
Connected old screen and there is no image. Tested with another known good display and still no image/backlight. 

When internal display is connected and external display all works fine on external but won’t detect internal display.

Checked that ‘new’ display on another MacBook and again Apple logo > progress bar > blank screen but when connected old screen all works fine.

EDP_PANEL_PWR_EN = 0V

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message:
Did PRAM reset?
New LCD assembly got from China, crappy like always.

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message:
PRAM reset did not help. Display is not detected and thats has been tested with original cracked screen and good known display. PRAM reset every time. Checked with new LCD flex cable as well.

Any idea?

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: Check if 3V3_S0SW_LCD appear, at least in the first few seconds.

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: There is only very short spike just after chime. Multimeter is slow but it show spike around 4V (tested without display).

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: Don't get Apple logo few seconds, like before?

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: Was the battery disconnected, before touching LCD connector?

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: So actually no image at all on internal LCD, but has video on external monitor?

title: 820-00923 no display after screen replacement
message: If you get pulse at 3V3/5V_S0SW_LCD, check for pulse at DP_INT_HPD at same time.
